label: A3BC8D2E2_oC64_36_3a_a_4b_b_2a-001
title: Uncharged NaV$_{2}$(PO$_{4}$)$_{2}$F$_{3}$ (NVPF) Structure
comments:
\href{current_web_home_dir/A3B5C8D2E2_oC80_63_cg_c2f_2h_e_g-001}{Na$_{3}$V$_{2}$(PO$_{4}$)$_{2}$F$_{3}$} and \href{current_web_home_dir/A3BC8D2E2_oC64_36_3a_a_4b_b_2a-001}{NaV$_{2}$(PO$_{4}$)$_{2}$F$_{3}$} (this structure) are repectively the fully charged and uncharged end points of an Na-ion positive electrode material. 
 In addition to these structures, (Mukherjee, 2020) synthesized Na$_{3}$V$_{2}$(PO$_{4}$)$_{2}$F$_{3}$ in two new forms: \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B4C8D2E2_tP76_136_fj_2i_2jk_de_j-001}{a ``flower'' arrangement, NVPF-F} and \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B3C8D2E2_oP72_58_gh_3g_4h_ef_h-001}{a ``hollow microsphere,'' NVPF-S}. 
 In this sample of uncharged NaV$_{2}$(PO$_{4}$)$_{2}$F$_{3}$ the Na I (4a) site is 88\% filled.
